text: one of the best coffee and tea I've had. friendly uncle and auntie too. I've seen them pack multiple bags of drinks for customers who buy a week's of drinks worth at one shot to store in the fridge and drink over the week, because it's that good.

Definitely a good cuppa of the c and good value.

A consistent crowd with a quick serving time.
One of the better hawker centre Kopi stalls that flies under the radar - note the queue of people most times of the day.. Good Kopi C and kaya buns.
